title: False advertising! Not only essential oils. Chemical fragrance.
text:
False advertising!

I only use products that are scented with essential oils. I have been doing that for over a decade. As soon as my husband opened the package across the room I could tell there was a chemical perfume in this product.

I read the entire description before ordering this product to make sure it is only scented with essential oils. The description on the website is very misleading. This is dangerous. Some chemicals make my throat close. Thankfully this one is just obnoxious and gross. But it absolutely makes this product completely worthless.

The ingredient list on the back of the bar conveniently lists "and select fragrance" at the end. That is where the chemical fragrance is hidden. I should have realized the seller was being sketchy when there was no photograph of the ingredients list included in their gallery. Usually that is enough to keep me from ordering a product. But I believed their description of it being scented by essential oils.

This bar could have been great. But they turned it into garbage by adding chemical fragrance. I would have let it slide and just returned it if they hadn't misrepresented their product in the description.

Buyer beware.

title: Protection, balance, and power
text:
This is a nice looking bracelet. I got the hematite/obsidian/evil eye. It is double row. It is packaged in a little plastic case and comes with a polishing cloth. It is supposed to give you power from the tiger's eye/evil eye, protection from the obsidian, and balance from the hematite. Whether you buy into that or not is your business. I tend to be a bit of a new age hippie, and I think belief powers strong energies, both positive and negative. I try to do what I can to promote as much positive energy as I can while deflecting the negative.
As far as protection, I need all that I can get.
This bracelet is pretty chic and nice looking. I'm not sure it goes with everything, but I will probably wear it just about everywhere. Unfortunately, my work has a no jewelry policy, so I can't wear it there. It is also reasonably priced and affordable for just about anyone.
The only downside I've found is the cinch. It is a cinch knot with an obsidian bead on each end. It's common enough in bracelets like this, and tightens and loosens easily enough. The only problem (see my picture) is that after cinching, you end up with quite a bit of string and the two beads hanging down. They can be tucked under, and I suppose I will do this, but I'm worried about catching it on something. The string seems fairly durable, and I hope it holds up.
5 stars for the idea, looks, and price of the bracelet minus one star for the cinching mechanism. A solid 4 stars for me.

The half versions have truly liquid movement that provides an indescribable feeling that gives me such relief when I feel the tension of my anxiety. I now carry the full sized version Half Thought (have had it over a year now and it's like new), as well as this “medium” version wherever I go. Try stainless half versions and you'll thank me. Especially if you experience anxiety and tenseness. A truly amazing little object. I never, ever thought I'd write a review of these rings. Once you hold the slightly weighted stainless steel versions, you will be sold. I've handed both versions to co-workers after they've looked at me like I'm nuts for always having these. The second I drop either in their hand, they get it... Hard to explain until you experience the stainless half versions compared to the anodized aluminum versions. The stainless versions have a weight to them that tops the cake. Get one. If you want to really let off some stress, get the large Half Thought. As it has thicker, stronger steel rings.

Buy either Half Thought (slightly larger and thicker rings), or this medium version. I guarantee you'll love em!

Keep up the great work, Geoff!

title: Beautiful and Unique; Well Worth the Price
text:
I ordered this because of its unique pattern and purple color. It seemed a little on the expensive side, but it was to wrap a special gift for my wife so I felt justified in the expense.

When it arrived, all doubts as to it's value were erased.

It came in a nice package with a Moonie Garcia logo sticker on the outside. Inside was the wrapping paper, packed in beautiful purple shredded packing paper. There was also a personalized thank you card from Moonie.

The paper itself is beautiful, with an antique, handmade feel to it. I would liken it to handmade wrapping paper from decades ago; much different than current, mass-produced wrapping paper. The purple color was rich and just the right shade, and has a matte finish, so there isn't any gloss or shine, which lends to the antique feel. The printed bat pattern manages to look both hand printed but perfectly uniform without any smudges or blurs.

Even the packing paper was high-quality, and I used it inside of the gift box, which improved the presentation of my own gift.

Overall, this was the perfect choice. The quality of the items and the entire ordering and opening experience was well worth the cost. It made the presentation and opening of my wife's gift unforgettable. I will absolutely be ordering futher items from Moonie Garcia again and next time I will make sure to order some ribbon to match.

title: Great training tool, but not a dog toy.
text:
My dogs and I are very fortunate to have a cottage on a lake. We love being in and around water all summer. Who doesn't? Ducks and geese also love being around water. Ducks and geese also love to poop. For some reason my dogs love duck and geese poop. They hoover it up. YUK! I thought this was a mildly disgusting but also fairly harmless pastime for my canine companions until they both caught intestinal parasites. Intestinal parasites lead to explosive diarrhea. Goodbye harmless pastime.

I am not a duck hunter, but I would like my dogs to chase ducks and geese! This takes some training as they (a German Shepherd Dog and Border Terrier) love to chase four legged creatures but are often less than interested in 2 legged creatures with wings.

The HuntEmUp Ultimate Duck Dog Training Dummy is a great tool for training. My dogs love to chase and retrieve anything thrown into the water on a hot day, or any day for that matter. This imitation duck is realistic in size and feel as advertised, but it definitely requires supervision. If left to her own devices, my GSD would destroy it fairly quickly and I'm sure my terrier would love to do the same thing. This is not a chew toy. Also, the rope, advertised as "premium" is great for throwing but would not last long in the mouth of any dog worth his or her chewing salt.

If your goals are training, water exercise, retrieval and hunting water foul, I think this is a great tool.

It's definitely not for unsupervised play.

title: Unusual style
text:
I was intrigued by the simple, but elegant design of these earrings. I like that they are 925 sterling silver and that they are handmade, presumably in the USA. I was concerned about whether they would bend and become misshapen when I put them in my ears. I decided to order the earrings and give them a try, despite my reservations.

I need not have worried. The earrings are quiet strong and are definitely not flimsy. I tried to gently twist them but they held their shape. I did struggle at first to orientate them in order to get them in my ears. I found that looking in a mirror while putting them in helped with that and I soon got the hang of it. They looked great. I wore them all day and they were very comfortable. I was a little worried that they might get tangled in my long hair, but that wasn't a problem.

In conclusion, these are an attractive quality unusual pair of earrings, that are well made, retain their shape and are comfortable to wear. What more can you ask of them?

title: Pretty but confusing
text:
I thought that these earring looked very nice and ordered them, despite not really knowing anything about them. The description is very confusing. The description mentions pearl, crystal, 925 sterling silver and 18K stamped. I believe that these are all incorrect. I believe that the stone is jade and that the metal is possibly gold plated silver. The metal is not stamped, so I do not believe it is 18K gold or 925 sterling silver. Because of the confusing description, I reduced the rating by one star.

I do believe that these earrings are hypoallergenic as I am sensitive to nickel, and have worn them without any problem. They are very pretty and I just love both the metal flower and the green jade stone. I think the design is unusual and very attractive. I do plan to wear these with my green and gold dress, as I think they will look amazing with it.

If you do not care about the inaccurate description, these earrings are a great purchase. They would also make an excellent gift.

title: Crane pearls are excellent
text:
This is the third Crane Pearl jewelry that I have ordered. I now own a pair of earrings, a string of pearls and this beautiful necklace. As far as I am concerned, you cannot go wrong if you order Crane jewelry. The item arrives in a nice gift box, with a cleaning cloth. The jewelry looks just like the product photos and the product descriptions are accurate. In other words, you know exactly what you are getting.

I love the quality of this necklace. The pearl has a beautiful luster and is just the right size. The cubic zirconia are small but they sparkle. The chain is marked 925 for sterling silver and is delicate but sturdy. This necklace is such a simple but stunning design and looks amazing. It is a piece of jewelry that will match virtually any outfit. I have not taken this necklace off since it arrived about a week ago. It is just what I wanted it for an everyday piece of jewelry that looks and feels great to wear. It would also look great if worn for special occasions.

I highly recommend this beautiful necklace. Buy it for yourself or give it as a present to a friend or relative.

title: Beautiful necklace.
text:
This string of beads is advertised for men, but as I think women would be interested in wearing it too. I thought that it could not be as stunning as show in the photos on the product page. In actual fact, it is just as beautiful as shown. The design, quality and workmanship are excellent. It comes in a very nice gift box, for those who want to give the beads as a present.

I highly recommend this quality item, to wear or to give as a gift.

The earrings came in a gift box, with an accompanying gift bag and cleaning cloth. These 6-7mm cultured pearls are simply beautiful. I love the simplicity and elegance of the design. title: Real amber beads
text:
I love the color of these beads and was excited to get them in. I thought amber came in only one color, so I did a Google search and discovered that there are different colors of amber, some rarer than others. One of the first things I did, when I received them, was try them on. They are beautiful. Like any good beads, the string is knotted between each bead. The connector is plastic, but that is so that when you secure the beads around your neck, the connection is hidden. Just be sure to screw in, not push in, the plastic connector.
I measured the necklace. It is 18 inches or 44 cm long. The product heading says it is 17 inches long but this is typo, which needs to be corrected. I wanted to see if these were really amber, and not plastic beads. I decided not to use a hot needle to see if they would melt. Instead, I used the density test. I dissolved 1/8 cup of salt in 1 cup of warm water, until it was fully dissolved. I lowered the necklace into the solution. To my delight, the necklace floated. The beads are real amber.
In conclusion, I am really happy with this item and hope to wear it often.

text:
I made the decision to purchase a sturdier eye patch to replace the cheap foam and fabric ones I have been using.

This handmade patch showed up in my mailbox this afternoon, the first day of the "will deliver by" date range. It is solidly constructed and will definitely outlast the ones I've been using. The hardware is metal, as are the connection points where the leather straps connect to the patch and where the buckle is connected to the end of the strap. There isn't a single stitch of thread in this entire piece and all of the connections are solid. I wasn't sure if the strap was going to fit, as my head is on the larger side of the size range, but it fits very well. There is enough material after the last hole that I could add another half inch if my head swells for some reason.

I've only worn it for about an hour today but it is very comfortable and unobtrusive so far, and I don't see that changing. There are no rough spots in the areas where it touches the skin and the leather is supple enough that it doesn't dig into my head.

I was expecting it to be more 'pirate' than 'Bond villian', and I am very glad that it looks like the latter instead of the former. Now maybe I'll get some respect around the office through intimidating looks.

30 DAY UPDATE - I'm still using the patch daily and have found that the strap has stretched a bit, making for a more comfortable and secure fit. Everything is as good as it was on day number one.

title: Vartiey Running lights for shoes & Sneakers Color Silver
text:
Review for: Running lights for shoes & sneakers Color Silver
I like these shoe lights. There are cute and they actually work. Once you removed the safety paper from in between the batteries. The lights also come with an extra set of batteries. They use the small round flat batters (also known as watch batteries). Inserting and removing the batteries is easy. These shoe lights can be used on most shoes. They are not the kind that can only be used on crocks. They clip on to the tongue of your shoes. You may even be able to clip them on to your laces. I put the lights on my slippers, and they stayed. attached,
To turn the lights on or off you just push the center of the light. There are 3 settings a steady light, and 2 pulse speeds (slow & Fast) one drawback is that you have to cycle through all of the light setting to turn them off. But it only takes a few seconds to turn then on or off. Another drawback is that these running shoe lights are on the expensive side. Even with having the extra set of batteries included. I doubt I would buy the lights for a child unless they were really good about keeping up and taking care of their stuff. But if you have the money to spend, these running shoe lights are helpful and they would make a great gift for people who run, jog, or walk at night.
